methods.getPartitionKeys:
Get the set of available partition keys.

:return: (java.util.Set<java.lang.String>) The set of available partition keys
methods.getPartitionValue:
Lookup the value of one of the table partitions enclosing the location keyed by this.

:param partitionKey: (java.lang.String) - The name of the partition
:return: (PARTITION_VALUE_TYPE) The partition value

text:
Base ImmutableTableLocationKey implementation for table locations that may be enclosed by partitions.
 Sub-classes should be sure to invoke the partition-map comparator at higher priority than other comparisons when
 implementing Comparable.compareTo(Object), and to include the partitions in their Object.equals(Object)
 implementations.
